<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586557>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 23. Progyrolepis heyleri POPLIN, 1999. a – a scale from the middle part of the lateral side of the body with conspicuous ridges arranged diagonally across the scale. MHK 82831, whitened. Scale bar 1 mm. b – small tubercles which form the microsculpture on the scale have elliptical base, antero-posteriorly elongated, and are arranged diagonally in the same direction as the ridges on Text-fig. 23a. MHK 82831. Scale bars 100 μm. c, d – photograph and drawing of a scale with a pore of the lateral sensory line. D 08.02.98.10.4/4, whitened. Scale bar 1 mm. e – drawing of a scale from the middle part of the lateral side of the body. D 04.11.95.10. Scale bar 1 mm. f – drawing of a scale from the anterior region of the body above the lateral sensory line. D 05.09.98. Scale bar 1 mm. g – drawing of a scale from the lateral side of the body between the lateral sensory line and the base of the pelvic fin. D 18.13.96.7. Scale bar 1 mm. h – drawing of a scale from the abdominal region of the body in front of the pelvic fin. BX 31.05.99.49. Scale bar 1 mm. i – large basal fulcra from the dorsal rim of the caudal peduncle. BX 28.01.99.8. Scale bar 5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4586557/files/figure.png" .

