<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586533>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 11. Progyrolepis heyleri POPLIN, 1999. a – set of bones of the left side of the cheek demonstrates the strong lower jaw, maxilla and preoperculum of old specimen. Large anterior regions of the preoperculum and maxilla are without sculpture, they were covered by the jugale. D 04.10.98.5. Scale bar 5 mm. b, c – photograph and drawing of the left maxilla of juvenile specimen D 13.04.97.6 with conspicuous horizontal lamina,whitened. Scale bars 5 mm. Abbreviations: Art– articulare; Aup –autopalatinum; Cor – coronoid; De – dentalospleniale; hlm – horizontal lamina of preoperculum; Mx – maxilla; Pop – preoperculum; popc – preopercular canal." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4586533/files/figure.png" .
